---
title: Tooltips
---

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
  	<h1>Tooltips</h1>
  	<h2>Standard Tooltips</h2>
    <p>Tooltips use the text from the <code>title</code> attribute and placement from the <code>data-placement</code> attribute. All tooltips must include the <code>data-toggle="tooltip"</code> attribute.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <div class="example">
      <a class="Button" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Tooltip on top">Top Tooltip</a>
      <a class="Button" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="right" title="Tooltip to the right">Right Tooltip</a>
      <a class="Button" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="bottom" title="Directions - there are two ways in which you can go about doing this.">Bottom Longer Tooltip</a>
    </div>
    <pre>
      <code><%= display_code('
<a class="Button" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="right" title="Tooltip to the right">Right Tooltip</a>') %></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
  	<h2>Hints</h2>
    <p>Hints provide additional information next to a paragraph or header.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <div class="example">
      <p>Have a question? <span class="Hint" data-placement="top" title="Look at me!" data-toggle="tooltip"></span></p>
    </div>
    <pre>
      <code><%= display_code('
<p>Have a question? <span class="Hint" data-placement="top" title="Look at me!" data-toggle="tooltip"></span></p>') %></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>
